  DATABASE INTEGRATION GUIDE
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  When you're ready to swap the in-memory test data for a real database, here
  is exactly what needs changing. The JS logic, UI, and interactions stay the
  same — only these entry points need to talk to your API.

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  TABLES YOU NEED TO CREATE
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Table: maps
  ┌──────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ column           │ type / notes                                         │
  ├──────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ id               │ VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY (use UUID or a slug)             │
  │ name             │ VARCHAR NOT NULL                                     │
  │ image_url        │ TEXT — store a CDN URL (S3, Cloudinary, etc.)        │
  │                  │ NOT base64 — base64 is fine for testing only         │
  │ width            │ INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 900                         │
  │ height           │ INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 600                         │
  │ created_at       │ TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()                              │
  │ updated_at       │ TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()                              │
  └──────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Table: pins  (one row per pin)
  ┌──────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ column           │ type / notes                                         │
  ├──────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ id               │ VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY                                  │
  │ map_id           │ VARCHAR REFERENCES maps(id) ON DELETE CASCADE        │
  │ material_id      │ VARCHAR — must match a key in MATERIALS[] above      │
  │ x                │ INTEGER NOT NULL                                     │
  │ y                │ INTEGER NOT NULL                                     │
  │ location_name    │ VARCHAR NOT NULL                                     │
  │ note             │ TEXT                                                 │
  └──────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Table: materials  (optional — currently hardcoded in MATERIALS[])
  You can keep materials hardcoded or move them to the DB.
  If you move them, add a GET /api/materials endpoint and populate
  MATERIALS[] on page load instead.

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  API ENDPOINTS NEEDED
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  GET    /api/maps              → returns array of map objects (with pins nested)
  POST   /api/maps              → creates a new map, returns the created object
  PUT    /api/maps/:id          → updates name, image_url, width, height
  DELETE /api/maps/:id          → deletes map + all its pins (cascade)

  POST   /api/maps/:id/pins     → creates a pin, returns the created pin
  PUT    /api/maps/:id/pins/:pinId  → updates materialId, locationName, note, x, y
  DELETE /api/maps/:id/pins/:pinId  → deletes a single pin

  Image upload (choose one):
    Option A — upload directly to S3/Cloudinary from the browser, store the URL.
    Option B — POST /api/maps/:id/image with multipart/form-data, server uploads
               to storage and returns the URL to store in maps.image_url.

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
