  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  TIPS
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  - Pin x/y are stored in the map's coordinate space (0..width, 0..height).
    On the user side, pins are rendered at absolute pixel positions so the
    map-inner div must always be sized to map.width × map.height exactly.
    If you resize a map, existing pin coordinates stay correct because they're
    already in the same coordinate system.

  - MATERIALS[] can stay hardcoded unless you need admins to add new materials.
    If you add a materials table, make sure material_id in the pins table is
    validated against it.

  - Operators and weapons (OPERATORS[], WEAPONS[]) are user-facing only.
    They don't need a DB table unless you want admins to manage them too.

  - The user's plans, checkedMats, and highlightMat are session-only state.
    If you want users to save their progress, store plans in localStorage or
    a user_plans table keyed by user session / account.

